<P>So was I rightly puni&s;hed in my journey to York, by undergoing &s;hame, fatigue, and the ha|zard of my health, while I po&s;&s;e&s;&s;ed a plenty to have prevented any one of tho&s;e vexations; for I &s;uf|f<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter">r<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter">d my&s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter">lf to be hoi&s;ted from my dog-kennel <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="2 letters">r two days, &s;tage after &s;tage: but as under the
