<P>Saturday, May 14, the Fair Penitent&mdash;Hora|to, Mr. Wilkin&s;on; Lothario, Mr. Frod&s;ham; and the Minor.&mdash;Tue&s;day, May 17, 1763, the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter">a&s;on fini&s;hed for my benefit, with the Jealous Wife, and Duke and no Duke.&mdash;I acted Oakley and Trappolin; but depended on the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="2 letters">cce&s;s of my never failing Tea as to attrac|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="2 letters">on.&mdash;I was favoured with a crowded audi|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter">nce, both before and behind the curtain; for <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="2 letters">e &s;tage was filled with gentlemen<NOTE N="*" PLACE="foot">At that time admittance behind the &s;cenes was allow|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="2 letters"> not only at benefits; but in general to the gentlemen <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 word"> frequented the boxes.</NOTE>; but my <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter">ea &s;calded their mouths, and though they were <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="2 letters">t ready to &s;et the hue and cry after me, as at Norwich, yet they grumbled much, and the next day I heard of nothing but what a &s;hame it was <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 word"> have made Mr. Wilkin&s;on &s;o fine a benefit, and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter"> return he only <HI>laughed</HI> at and in&s;ulted them <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 word"> <HI>hum, hum, hum.</HI> In &s;hort, it was evident in
